HEADWORD: Sapidness
<hw>Sap"id*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Quality of being sapid;
sapidity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the Israelites fancied the <qex>sapidness</qex> and relish of
the fleshpots, they longed to taste and to return.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

